From: HVM <hvm@hellmessage.com>
Subject: [PATCH] reds: always forward monitors config to vdagent

When the Windows VDagent sees a new monitor config, it triggers a refresh
of the display resolution. This is needed when the device driver does not
have the capability to see the resolution change directly from QEMU
(for example VirtIO GPU on ARM Win 11 with utmapp/virtio-gpu-wddm-dod),
and depends on VDagent to see the change.

Stock spice-server reds.cpp swallows AGENT_MSG_FILTER_MONITORS_CONFIG via
`return` after calling reds_on_main_agent_monitors_config — VDagent in
guest never sees the message, so SetDisplayConfig path is never triggered.

Change `return` to `break` so the message is also forwarded to vdagent
chardev (i.e. vdservice/vdagent.exe in guest).

This patch is identical to upstream UTM patch 09/11 in spice-0.14.3.patch
(authored by osy@turing.llc 2022-03-04), ported here to spice-server 0.16.0
(line shifted from 1256 in 0.14.3 to 1180 in 0.16.0).

Reference: /Volumes/DEVELOP/Github/UTM/patches/spice-0.14.3.patch
           commit message "reds: always send monitors config"

---
 server/reds.cpp | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/server/reds.cpp b/server/reds.cpp
index 0000000..0000001 100644
--- a/server/reds.cpp
+++ b/server/reds.cpp
@@ -1177,7 +1177,7 @@ void reds_on_main_agent_data(RedsState *reds, MainChannelClient *mcc, const void
         return;
     case AGENT_MSG_FILTER_MONITORS_CONFIG:
         reds_on_main_agent_monitors_config(reds, mcc, message, size);
-        return;
+        break;
     case AGENT_MSG_FILTER_PROTO_ERROR:
         mcc->shutdown();
         return;
